To set up nanobulletin, run the "setup" script using:
   . setup 
   OR 
   source setup

What this does:

Create a virtualenv directory, i.e. "virtualenv venv" and activate it with ". venv/bin/activate".

Install Flask in the virtualenv by running "pip install Flask".

setup.py just does the following in order to initialize the db:
	import nanob
	nanob.init_db()